<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Spot2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Spot,</orth> vb. 1) to mark with a colour different from the ground; only in the partic. <emph>--ed</emph>: <cit><quote>--ed snakes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed livers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 18</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the --ed die,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 34</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a handkerchief --ed with strawberries,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.435" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 435</bibl></cit>.*<lb />2) to stain, to taint: <bibl n="shak. luc 196" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 196" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 196</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 196" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 196</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 95.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 95, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.328" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 328</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.283" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 283</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 5.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 1, 36</bibl>. <emph>--ed</emph> == polluted, guilty: <cit><quote>this --ed and inconstant man,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 110</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>their --ed souls,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 134</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed, detested and abominable,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 74</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>let die the --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 4, 35</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Toad-spotted.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>